resource_data.title: Wildlife Habitat Incentives Program (WHIP) In Alabama
resource_data.creator: Natural Resources Conservation Service
resource_data.keywords: Conservation, Resource management, Regeneration (ecosystems), Terrestrial ecosystems, Environments, Habitats
resource_data.description: A voluntary program designed to help people develop and enhance habitat for fish and wildlife on private lands. Wildlife Habitat Incentives Program (WHIP) provides both technical assistance and cost-share funds.
